🎯 Core Objectives
The project is built around four high-impact goals, each targeting a specific gap in traditional hotel revenue management:

Demand Forecasting — Leverages historical booking data and time-series predictive modeling to accurately forecast room demand across different seasons, local events, and market conditions. This allows hotel administrators to prepare staffing, inventory, and pricing well in advance of fluctuating demand periods.

Dynamic Pricing Optimization — Implements intelligent algorithms that recommend real-time adjustments to room rates based on current occupancy levels, competitor pricing intelligence, and available inventory. The goal is to ensure the hotel always captures the maximum willingness-to-pay at any given point in time, directly driving up Average Daily Rate (ADR) and RevPAR.

Cancellation Prediction — Develops classification models that assign a cancellation risk probability to each incoming booking based on factors like lead time, booking channel, guest type, and deposit status. This early warning system allows management to enforce strategic overbooking policies or launch targeted retention campaigns before revenue is lost.

Customer Segmentation — Analyzes guest demographics, geographic origins, and behavioral patterns to identify distinct customer profiles. These segments enable personalized marketing campaigns, channel-specific offers, and tailored service experiences that increase both conversion rates and guest satisfaction.

