Why Power BI? Power BI was selected as the core platform due to its end-to-end capabilities — from data ingestion and transformation via Power Query, to complex metric calculation via DAX, to rich interactive visualization and AI-enhanced analytics. Its cloud-based sharing via Power BI Service enables seamless collaboration across Executive, Marketing, and Operations stakeholders without requiring any additional infrastructure.

DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) was used extensively to build automated measures for critical KPIs including:

Average Daily Rate (ADR)
Revenue Per Available Room (RevPAR)
Occupancy Percentage
Realisation Percentage
Year-over-Year (YoY) Revenue Growth
Power Query handled all upstream data engineering tasks including null value treatment, duplicate removal, categorical encoding, and date standardization to ensure a clean, reliable single source of truth before any modeling or visualization was performed.

🏗️ Data Architecture — Star Schema
The backbone of HotelRevAI is a carefully engineered Star Schema data model, designed for both analytical performance and scalability.

Fact Tables (Transactional Data):

Fact_Bookings — Stores transaction-level booking records including guest type, room category, lead time, booking channel, meal plan, and stay duration.
Fact_Daily_Revenue — Captures daily financial snapshots including ADR, RevPAR, total revenue, and occupancy figures for trend analysis.
Dimension Tables (Descriptive Context):

Dim_Date — A dedicated Calendar Table built to support rich temporal analysis across Day of Week, Month, Quarter, and Fiscal Year dimensions. This is essential for identifying seasonal patterns and weekday vs. weekend behavior.
Dim_Customer — Contains guest demographic details including market segment, country of origin, guest type (Adult/Family), and repeat guest status.
Dim_Room — Covers room type classifications, bed configurations, upgrade trends, and room-level revenue contributions.
Dim_Hotel — Differentiates between City Hotels and Resort Hotels, enabling property-level performance comparisons.
The Star Schema with 1-to-many relationships between dimension and fact tables reduced data redundancy, simplified DAX measure logic, and increased dashboard refresh speeds by 30% compared to a flat, denormalized data structure.

